Title:
------
AUKBC Tokenizer  1.0

Description: 
------------

AUKBC Tokenizer v1.0: This takes a text file in UTF-8 as input. The sentences and tokens are indentifed and split. 


Requirements (Pre-requisites):
-----------------------------
a)Operating System		:    LINUX/UNIX system (preffered Ubuntu 14.04 LTS)

b)Compiler/Interpreter/Librarie(s):    Perl (v 5.18 or higher) and C++ compiler (gcc 3.0 or higher)

c) The input file is in UTF-8 encoding. 
   The input file format should be as shown in sample_input.txt


Directory Structure:
--------------------

Tokenizer
     |
     |---License.txt
     |---README (How to run/use. The file that you are reading now.)
     |---tokenizer-splitter-v1.pl (core tokenizer engine)
     |---notbesplittedwords.txt (resource file)
     |---sample_input.txt (reference input file)
     |---sample_output.txt (reference output file)
     

Installation:
-------------
There is no special installation required for this. Copy paste the folder in any place in your system and start using.

How to Use?
------------
The format of the input file should be as shown in the sample file 'sample_input.txt'. The encoding of the file should be in utf-8. 

	$ perl tokenizer-splitter-v1.pl < sample_input.txt > sample_output.txt

The output will be written in the standard ouput ('>')

Limitation:
-----------
This will not handle the section and sub-section headings which are not delimited by a dot (.). 


